<!-- HOW TO BUDGET GENERAL QUESTION-->
<!-- ============================== -->
<div>
  <h3>How to Budget!</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Track your income:
        <p>Do you have a stable income? Fixed income?</p>
      </li>
      <li>Identify how you are spending money:
        <p>Where are your expenses going? What are you buying? What is non-negotiable and what is negotiable?</p>
      </li>
      <li>Add up the amounts of your regular expenses and deduct that from your paycheck:
      <p>If you get a negative number you are spending too much and need to cut back. If you have money left over then you can split that up into groups. ie savings, emergency, projects, trips etc.</p>
      </li>
      <li>Create your budget:
        <p>These should be short-term budget goals like not spending more than a certain amount of money every month or saving a few hundred dollars every month. Also should have long-term goals such as being able to put down a mortgage payment on a home or make a vehicle payment or pay off credit cards completely.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>Make a list of non-negotiable bills and needs:
        <p>These are deducted from your income first.</p>
      </li>
      <li>Make a list of negotiable wants and include luxuries:
        <p>These are deducted from your income last. Remember there is a differents between wants and needs. Can you redude these expenses?</p>
      </li>
      <li>Finally: Maintain your budget:
        <p>Don't go over budget, keep your checkbook updated regularly, don't count on bonuses or tax refunds.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>

</div>
